# ============================================================================
# JobSearch_Camunda — .gitignore
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Strategy (decided 2026-06-28): local git, PERSONAL DATA NEVER COMMITTED.
# The repo tracks the *system* — methodology (Process/), AI operating
# instructions, and the new /docs blueprint. It does NOT track personal
# career data (CVs, profile, application tracker, captured job descriptions).
# When the SaaS app is built, that personal data becomes gitignored SEED data.
# ============================================================================

# --- Personal / sensitive career data (NEVER COMMIT) -----------------------
# Anchored to repo root: macOS is case-insensitive, so an unanchored `Profile/`
# also ignores app paths like `app/profile/`. Match ONLY the top-level personal dirs.
/Profile/
/Group CVs/
/Job Descriptions/
/Job Hunting Lists.xlsx

# Any stray personal binaries anywhere in the tree
*.xlsx
*.docx
*.doc
*.pdf
*.url
*.canvas
*.drawio
*.Rmd
*.rmd
# NOTE: personal *.html (e.g. Profile/Testing-R.html) is already covered by the
# Profile/ ignore above. The docs/ review pages (.html) ARE tracked deliverables.

# Future SaaS seed data (extracted from the workbooks — see docs/DEPLOYMENT.md)
/app/**/seed/data/
/supabase/seed/data/
seed/data/

# --- Secrets ---------------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.key
*.pem

# --- OS / editor -----------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp

# --- Claude Code local settings (keep shared settings.json if added later) --
.claude/settings.local.json

# --- Local agent / skill tooling (not part of the app) ---------------------
.agents/
.claude/skills/
skills-lock.json

# --- Local-only bucket: design-input, launch videos, scratch, scaffolding -----
# Consolidated here so they don't clutter the repo root; kept on disk, never
# committed. Nothing in the app reads from _local/. See _local/README.md.
/_local/

# --- Bulky one-off handoff artifacts ---------------------------------------
*.zip

# --- Node / Next.js / Supabase (for the upcoming app phases) ---------------
node_modules/
.next/
out/
build/
dist/
# Root-anchored: the test-coverage report dir at the repo root only. WITHOUT the
# leading slash this also matched app/profile/coverage/, silently excluding that
# route from git (and every deploy) while it still ran locally off-disk.
/coverage/
*.tsbuildinfo
next-env.d.ts
.vercel/
/.storage/
.turbo/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
.supabase/
.obsidian/
fix-email.ts
Pasted image*.png
*.tsbuildinfo
/templates

certificates

# --- Playwright MCP (browser-driven AI capture, A.3) ------------------------
# The persistent login profile itself lives OUTSIDE the repo by default
# (%LOCALAPPDATA%\ms-playwright-mcp\mcp-{channel}-{hash} on Windows — verified
# 2026-07-23), so there's nothing there to ignore. This is just the tool's
# per-run snapshot/console-log output dir, written into the project root.
/.playwright-mcp/